               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1326" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1326" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1326" type="surname" value="HALLAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1326" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH HALLAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Edward Hallam, oilman, Shepperton-street, New North-road. About seven o'clock on Monday evening, the 20th</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184311270168"></xptr>
               <p>of Nov., I was in my parlour behind the shop—a man came in to buy some tobacco, and I heard him say, "What do you want here?"—I rose up, and caught the prisoner by his head, coming from under the flap of the counter—I found the till on the ground, about two yards from its place, and all the money gone—there had been about ten shillings, ten sixpences, and some coppers—I called the policeman, but no one came—there were two more persons outside the shop—they all got away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1327" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1327" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1327" type="surname" value="PARKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1327" type="given" value="PHILIP"></interp>PHILIP PARKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I was going into the shop for tobacco, and saw the pri<lb></lb>soner coming from under the flap of the counter—there were two other young men outside—I heard a whistle, and they all ran away—I pursued them, but could not catch them—they kicked me about—I am quite sure the prisoner is the person—he was not taken that evening.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1328" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1328" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1328" type="surname" value="WESTBURY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1328" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WESTBURY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 215.) I was on duty that evening in plain clothes, and saw three men and two boys coming in a direction from the prosecutor's—I watched them through Hoxton—one of them went to a public-house, and got change, and gave some of the boys some money—the prisoner is one of the boys.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was not there.</p>
